<td><b>Areas on which to focus: The difference between hardware and software, Examples of software vs. hardware, Main memory vs. Secondary Memory, What is an Operating System</b><br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;Note: most computers do not have floppy disks anymore and the new Ultrabook laptops do not even have hard drives.  Instead, they have Flash memory (like a bunch of USB memory sticks inside) to store things. Ultrabooks&nbsp;<span style="font-size:13.3333330154419px;line-height:21.3333320617676px">are intended to be used in an environment with a robust internet connection. &nbsp;Therefore they&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:13.3333330154419px;line-height:21.3333320617676px">do not need as much memory since they&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:10pt;line-height:1.6;background-color:transparent">use applications residing on the Web and store files in the Cloud.</span></td>
